job_description:
Break/Fix Technician

Our customer is looking for a Break/Fix Technician who will work in a manufacturing/factory environment to troubleshoot hardware (laptops, PCs, peripherals) and software (Windows/Office) for Boeing and Dell end users. Successful candidates will be expected to follow established documented processes, perform software and hardware break/fix including disconnecting computing equipment and networking equipment during factory changes. Candidate will help customers via phone, in person and remotely. Occasional travel to different local sites (mileage is reimbursed; reliable means of transportation is required). Position potentially requires a lot of walking in Factory and Flight-line areas. This position is part of a team supporting our customer 24x7 with multiple shifts, responding to tasks associated to SLA/SLO (Service Level) agreements.


Responsibilities

  1. Primary Responsibility - Perform onsite troubleshooting, repairs and upgrades for client hardware and software resolution.
  2. Provide Installation, Moves, Additions, Changes, and Dispose Activities upon request
  3. Perform hands-on and in-depth troubleshooting and associated repairs of failed client hardware and software.
  4. Perform thorough documentation of all service activities.
  5. Meets all success-measuring benchmarks (customer services, SLO / SLA’s, etc.…)


Qualifications:

  1. A+ Certification required (or equivalent hands on experience of 2 years full time, hardware maintenance), Net+ Certification recommended
  2. Experience troubleshooting and repairing basic networking issues
  3. Demonstrate good customer service skills
  4. Ability to work independently and manage time to complete tasks
  5. Possess a valid driver’s license with reliable personal transportation to travel between supported sites
  6. Advanced hands-on experience troubleshooting & repairing client hardware.
  7. Possess strong communication skills; both verbal and written.
  8. 3+ years of relevant experience or equivalent combination of education and work experience.
  9. Some shifts may require one weekend day
  10. Be able to lift 35 lbs.
  11. Pass security and drug testing
minimumEducationLevel: Some training or study post high school

job_description:
Data Center Technician-IT Technician (DCT) Level 1


The Data Center Technician Level 1 is responsible for supporting the physical infrastructure and operational uptime of a data center. This includes staging, installing, maintaining, and decommissioning hardware such as servers, racks, switches, and drives. The technician follows standardized protocols to perform startups, shutdowns, diagnostics, and repairs, ensuring systems meet performance and safety requirements. The role also involves documenting work, escalating issues when necessary, and working non-standard hours including nights and weekends. Ideal candidates are reliable, technically inclined, and possess basic IT knowledge with a strong work ethic.

  1. Prepares, stages, sets up, and performs startups and shutdowns (e.g., racks, hard drives, switches) according to specific instructions, checklists, guides, standard protocols, and emails.
  2. Performs post-execution quality checks and verifies that grounding, staging, labeling, and cabling are set up properly according to safety protocols, deployment standards, and planned Network Design Tasks (NDTs).
  3. Performs diagnostics and troubleshooting following standard procedures, quickly identifies the cause(s) of issues, and replaces faulty components
  4. Decommissions hardware for simple changes and refreshes (e.g., memory upgrades, OS rebuilds) following standard procedures with minimal guidance
  5. Follows procedures to communicate, report, and escalate incidents to appropriate Datacenter Technician Leads
trainingRequirements: 1 year+ experience supporting IT equipment or related technology, Microsoft Office

Description

As an Operations Engineer, you will lead and manage the lifecycle of challenging cross-functional projects, developing and delivering the next generation of automation and material handling solutions. You are a customer obsessed leader that will play an integral part in planning and implementation of the facility network infrastructure including new builds, retrofits, expansions and program initiatives. Partnering with internal customers and internal/external stakeholders to engage as a team and ensure a timely handover will be part of your critical tasks.

As an Operations Engineer for Amazon, you will work with some of the most talented engineers in the design, development, and delivery of physical distribution systems around the globe. You are responsible for managing a technology or integration project, successfully delivering the solution to meet project goals. You may work directly with external equipment vendors, customers, or partners, and you have a solid understanding of the design approaches and industry technologies utilized in fulfillment and distribution center designs. To meet timelines and minimize disruption to support teams, you manage the overall schedule, proactively mitigate risks, and keep the scope of engineering deliverables under control.

Key job responsibilities
• Work independently with internal and external teams to successfully manage the lifecycle of challenging projects, and act as owner in delivering on project objectives and targets. Projects may span organizations or geographies in support of business objectives.
• Actively participate in firm engineering reviews, and make tangible impact on the proposed solutions on an individual system or its components, on the overall systems architecture, and on facility processes.
• Partner with internal teams, stakeholders and external vendors to set project priorities, establish milestones, and drive schedules to meet deadlines. Proactively assess stakeholders’ dependencies and milestones, problem-solve and drive solutions to mitigate the impact from the issues.
• Lead and coordinate all execution efforts in delivering systems and automated equipment designs per established standards and guidelines. Perform equipment/system installation, throughput and safety qualifications. Simplify, optimize, remove bottlenecks and provide feedback while resolving difficult system problems or technical deficiencies.
• Lead effective meetings by setting the objectives, putting the right people in the room and driving detailed business and technical discussions/alignment. Document meeting discussions, decisions and future steps, ensuring alignment on expectations with internal partner teams and outside vendors.
• Promptly and accurately communicate project status, risk analysis and risk mitigation plans. Effectively answer project questions in detail, and regularly produce clear and concise summaries for the project to leadership/management team.
• Competently articulate system and/or equipment designs, including layouts, technical specifications and functional capabilities to internal customers and partner teams.
• Support change order controls, purchase orders, and invoice validation/approvals.
• Excel at building strong working relationships with internal and external stakeholders across multiple projects.
• Identify and lead process improvement initiatives that improve the Engineering and cross-teams’ efficiencies, optimizing the teams’ value and delivery. Through collaboration, generate high-quality, cost-effective solutions in compressed periods of time.
• Travel 75% domestically although travel intensity can be variable and consist of up to three weeks in a row, including weekends.

Basic Qualifications
• Bachelor’s Degree in Industrial Engineering, Mechanical Engineering, or other STEM field
• 4+ years of experience as a Project Engineer, Process Engineer, Project Manager, Manufacturing Engineer, or related occupation
• Experience managing the lifecycle of cross-functional projects, implementing automated equipment and/or integrated systems
• Experience with CAD software (AutoCAD, REVIT, BIM 360, etc.)
• Experience supporting deployment of new product/technology and/or large material handling and automation installations in a construction environment to include safety and permitting requirements.

Preferred Qualifications
• Master’s degree in Engineering, Operations, Business Administration, or a related STEM field
• Operations Management/Distribution Center experience with direct management or responsibility for material handling, automation, or other technical projects
• Experience with Six Sigma and/or Lean Manufacturing
• Experience with Microsoft Project, Smartsheet programs
• Experience with new product introduction and/or implementation automation solutions, such as Conveyors, Sorters, high speed manufacturing and packaging lines, Robotic work cells
• Proven technical leadership for industrial engineering projects or program

It’s a great opportunity to apply your knowledge in AI and machine learning to real-world projects, collaborate with experienced engineers, and help shape the future of interactive AI systems.


Responsibilities:

Documentation & Architecture: Review, maintain, and update documentation related to the AI architecture to ensure clarity and accuracy.

Model Improvement: Propose and implement enhancements in AI reasoning models and workflows to improve decision-making and efficiency.

Prompt Management: Manage and refine initialization prompts for AI agents, optimizing how agents are prompted to achieve better responses.

Performance Optimization: Monitor AI agent performance and cost-efficiency, identifying bottlenecks and optimizing for speed and resource usage.

Tool Development: Develop tools or scripts to track and analyze AI agent interactions, using the insights to improve efficiency and response quality.

Model Deployment: Assist in deploying and maintaining AI models using OpenAI APIs, ensuring models are up-to-date and functioning correctly in production.

Cloud Integration: Work with Render.com (and similar cloud platforms) to deploy AI services and ensure seamless integration with our applications.

Experimentation: Conduct experiments and evaluations on AI agents to test improvements, aiming to boost response accuracy and reduce latency.

Research & Innovation: Continuously research emerging AI technologies, frameworks, and best practices to recommend and implement upgrades that enhance system efficiency and capabilities.

Debugging: Debug and troubleshoot issues within AI workflows and architecture, ensuring reliable AI agent operations.

Desired Qualifications:

Education: Currently pursuing or recently completed a degree in Computer Science, Artificial Intelligence, Machine Learning, or a related field.

Programming Skills: Proficiency in Python and familiarity with AI/ML libraries or frameworks.

OpenAI & ML Tools: Experience or coursework using OpenAI APIs and knowledge of AI model fine-tuning techniques.

Cloud Deployment: Familiarity with cloud platforms (especially Render.com) for deploying applications or AI models is a plus

Analytical Ability: Ability to analyze model performance metrics and optimize for better accuracy and efficiency.

Problem-Solving: A proactive, problem-solving mindset with keen attention to detail in debugging and optimizing systems.

Communication: Strong written and verbal communication skills for effective documentation and reporting on project progress and findings.

Preferred Qualifications:

Vector Databases: Experience with vector databases and knowledge retrieval systems for storing and querying AI knowledge bases.

Reinforcement Learning: Understanding of reinforcement learning techniques and how they can be applied to improve agent behavior.

AI Orchestration: Exposure to frameworks like LangChain or similar tools for orchestrating complex AI agent interactions.

Hands-on Experience: Previous experience in AI model deployment, testing, or participating in AI/ML projects (through coursework, personal projects, or prior internships).
